= doc_title(title: "Keyboard (KBD)", comp: @comp) do |title|
  %p
    Styled keyboard key representations for displaying keyboard shortcuts,
    hotkeys, and command references. Perfect for documentation, tutorials,
    and UI hints with realistic key styling and multiple size options.


= doc_example(title: "Basic Example") do |doc|
  - doc.with_description do
    :markdown
      The KBD component is used to display keyboard shortcuts and command
      references.

  = daisy_kbd do
    


= doc_example(title: "Various Sizes") do |doc|
  - doc.with_description do
    :markdown
      Keyboard indicators are available in four sizes: `kbd-xs`, `kbd-sm`,
      `kbd-md` (default), and `kbd-lg`.

  .my-2.flex.flex-row.gap-4.items-center
    = daisy_kbd(css: "kbd-lg") do
      Shift
    = daisy_kbd(css: "kbd-md") do
      Shift
    = daisy_kbd(css: "kbd-sm") do
      Shift
    = daisy_kbd(css: "kbd-xs") do
      Shift


= doc_example(title: "Inside a Sentence") do |doc|
  - doc.with_description do
    :markdown
      KBD components can be easily integrated into text to provide inline
      instructions or hints.

  .my-2.flex.flex-row.gap-2.items-center
    %p Press
    = daisy_kbd do
      F
    %p to pay respects.


= doc_example(title: "Combined Keys") do |doc|
  - doc.with_description do
    :markdown
      You can combine multiple KBD components with simple text separators to
      show multi-key shortcuts.

  .my-2.flex.flex-row.gap-2.items-center
    = daisy_kbd do
      Ctrl

    +

    = daisy_kbd do
      Alt

    +

    = daisy_kbd do
      Del


= doc_example(title: "Function Keys") do |doc|
  - doc.with_description do
    :markdown
      KBD components work perfectly with special characters and symbols for
      modifier keys.

  .my-2.flex.flex-row.gap-4.items-center
    = daisy_kbd do
      ⌘

    = daisy_kbd do
      ⌥

    = daisy_kbd do
      ⇧

    = daisy_kbd do
      ⌃


